    "□ Remark 5.7.",
    "Since the algorithm is entirely topological, a natural question which arises at this point is whether there is a simpler, direct topological proof of the fact that Φ(ρ) is an element of E Θ, which does not involve the Riemann-Hilbert-Birkhoff correspondence.",
    "Recall that the representation varieties E Θ and E Θ possess a quasi-Hamiltonian structure.",
    "We conjecture that these structures are preserved by the isomorphism induced by the Fourier transform.",
